10. Fetch available fees

POST <host>/rest/<store_code>/V1/activ-checkout/available-fees
Sample request

Payload:

{
    "addressInformation": {
        "address": {
            "region_id": 610,
            "country_id": "PL",
            "street": [
                "Graniczna 8b"
            ],
            "postcode": "54-610",
            "city": "Wrocław",
            "firstname": "Jan",
            "lastname": "Kowalski",
            "company": "Firma",
            "telephone": "987654321"
        },
        "shipping_carrier_code": "gls_poland",
        "shipping_method_code": "gls_poland"
    }
}

Headers:

{
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer <customer token>"
}

Response

Array of fees available for given quote.

Fee:
Field 	Type 	Description
id 	int 	fee id
description 	string 	fee description
required 	boolean 	is required to select at least one option
multiple 	boolean 	can select more than one option
current_value 	array 	array of fee option ids
options 	array 	array of objects representing fee options

Fee options:
Field 	Type 	Description
entity_id 	int 	fee option id
fee_id 	int 	fee id
price 	float 	fee price in quote currency (e.g. 15.45)
price_type 	string 	fixed or percent
default 	boolean 	is option selected by default
price_currency 	string 	currency of the price (same as quote currency)
label 	string 	fee option label
Sample response

[
    {
        "id": 7,
        "description": "<b>Description</b>: This field contains html with fee description",
        "required": true,
        "multiple": true,
        "current_value": [9],
        "options": [
            {
                "entity_id": 9,
                "fee_id": 7,
                "price": 15.15,
                "price_type": "fixed",
                "default": true,
                "label": "Label"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "id": 9,
        "description": "Description",
        "required": false,
        "multiple": false,
        "current_value": [],
        "options": [
            {
                "entity_id": 11,
                "fee_id": 9,
                "price": 0,
                "price_type": "fixed",
                "default": false,
                "label": "Label 2"
            }
        ]
    }
]

11. Set fees

POST <host>/rest/<store_code>/V1/activ-checkout/set-fees
Sample request

Payload:

{
    "feeId": 8,
    "optionIds": [10],
    "addressInformation": {
        "address": {
            "region_id": 610,
            "country_id": "PL",
            "street": [
                "Graniczna 8b"
            ],
            "postcode": "54-610",
            "city": "Wrocław",
            "firstname": "Jan",
            "lastname": "Kowalski",
            "company": "Firma",
            "telephone": "987654321"
        },
        "shipping_carrier_code": "gls_poland",
        "shipping_method_code": "gls_poland"
    }
}

Headers:

{
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer <customer token>"
}

Response

Totals for current quote. More information: docs

Extension attributes contains "activ_agreements" (which may differ from the Set parameters response if selected fees has changed).
Sample response

[
    {
        "id": 7,
        "description": "<b>Description</b>: This field contains html with fee description",
        "required": true,
        "multiple": true,
        "current_value": [9],
        "options": [
            {
                "entity_id": 9,
                "fee_id": 7,
                "price": 15.15,
                "price_type": "fixed",
                "default": true,
                "label": "Label"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "id": 9,
        "description": "Description",
        "required": false,
        "multiple": false,
        "current_value": [],
        "options": [
            {
                "entity_id": 11,
                "fee_id": 9,
                "price": 0,
                "price_type": "fixed",
                "default": false,
                "label": "Label 2"
            }
        ]
    }
]

12. Place order

POST <host>/rest/<store_code>/V1/carts/mine/payment-information
Sample request

Payload:

{
    "paymentMethod": {
        "method": "banktransfer",
        "extension_attributes": {
            "agreement_ids": [1,3],
            "external_number": "F0000123",
            "notification_email": "email-address@example.com"
        }
    }
}

Headers:

{
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer <customer token>"
}

Response

200 Success - order ID

400 Bad request 401 Unauthorized
Sample response

"450031"

More information: docs
13. Get order tracking statuses

POST <host>/rest/<store_code>/V1/orderTracking
Sample request

Payload: list of order IDs

{
    "orderIds" : ["450031", "450032", "450033"]
}

Headers:

{
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Authorization": "Bearer <customer token>"
}

Response

200 Success - list of orders with tracking data (only if order is from your company) 400 Bad request 401 Unauthorized
Sample response

[
    {
        "order_id": "1",
        "order_status": "delivered",
        "carrier": "GLS",
        "tracking_number": "123456",
        "delivered_at": "2022-06-30 20:10:45",
        "tracking_url": "https://www.gls-pakete.de/en/parcel-tracking?trackingNumber=123456" 
    },
    {
        "order_id": "2",
        "order_status": "shipped",
        "carrier": "Odbiór osobisty",
        "tracking_number": "123456",
        "delivered_at": null,
        "tracking_url": null
    }
]
